The two collapsed in the cells and died at Kimbimbi Sub-County Hospital.Police later said the two could have succumbed to Covid-19 complications. Investigations into the death of two remandees who collapsed at Wang'uru police station and later died in hospital have begun.
The probe kicks off following a post-mortem report that showed that Martin Musyoka, 58, and John Njeru, 28, may have succumbed to injuries inflicted at the station or lack of sufficient oxygen occasioned by congestion.



