According to Mwea East Sub-County police boss Daniel Kitavi, an inquest file has been opened by the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI).
"The DCI is now investigating the matter and we urge relatives of the two remand prisoners to be patient. We would like to establish who caused the death of the duo," he said.
Mr Kitavi said remandees and convicts who had been locked up in the same cell with the victims have been questioned and recorded statements.



