The two were arrested on November 20, 2020Â during a major crackdown on people who were flouting curfew rules imposed by the government to prevent the spread of Covid-19.
The two villagers were seized in Mikimaini and Thiba villages in Mwea East Sub-County and locked up at the police station.
However, the following day, they collapsed in the cells as they waited to be taken to court and were rushed to Kimbimbi Sub-County Hospital where they died.
Police later said the two could have succumbed to Covid-19 complications.
The county police commander Leah Kithei told the media that the remand prisoners fell sick when they were at the station and were taken to hospital.
She dismissed claims by relatives that they had been assaulted while in the cells.



