"This is a very old police station. It cannot serve the remand prisoners well. The station lacks adequate facilities like toilets while the cells are congested. Something urgent should be done to make the remand prisoners safe," Mr Koinange said.





The committee was shocked to find filthy and stinking toilets when it visited the station on Wednesday afternoon.
"The toilets, which have no doors for privacy, are overflowing with human waste. The situation is really bad," said Mr Koinange. It all started on November 20 when the two villagers were arrested and locked up for flouting curfew rules. Ezekiel Oduor Okiru, 20, was allegedly shot by police on patrol on Friday night for not wearing a mask. He allegedly received a sh200,000 bribe to approve the opening of a fuel station in Oyugis. Kabila had succeeded in forming an army with many generals said to still be loyal to him. This is the first time Uhuru is meeting Abiy since Addis Ababa launched a crackdown on TPLF.